data.description: Welcome to 2100 Chase Ave; this updated 1950s Cape Cod-style home in the city is ready for you to make it your home. As you enter the front door, you will be greeted by a spacious living room, with the primary bedroom and bathroom to your right. Turning to your left, you will find the original dining room currently used as a playroom. But you can transform it into whatever you desire, whether it be an additional living room space, a sitting room, or keep it a playroom. The updated kitchen and sizable dining room round out a fitting first-floor living home. Upstairs, there are two more bedrooms, and in the basement, you will find plenty of storage space, laundry room, and mechanicals. The backyard has recently been fenced and is perfect for playing, relaxing, or keeping your pets safe. Other notable features of this property include an additional off-street parking area that can accommodate up to four cars, two storage buildings, updated windows, and hardwood floors. Experience the charm of Chase Ave for yourself and schedule a visit today.
